  "title": "OPERATION MANAGER IN SHIPYARD",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>MIZU ENGINEERING SERVICES PTE. LTD.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Manage and lead daily site operations for projects involving 100–200 personnel, ensuring safe, timely, and compliant delivery within project scope.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and coordinate site operations to achieve project milestones while maintaining safety and quality standards</li><li>Develop and execute manpower planning and deployment strategies to optimize workforce productivity and discipline</li><li>Collaborate with supervisors, clients, and subcontractors to resolve operational challenges and align project objectives</li><li>Enforce compliance with regulatory, safety, and contractual requirements to mitigate risks and uphold standards</li><li>Prepare detailed operational and manpower reports to inform project tracking and decision-making</li></ul>",
